cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with the problem of monocular Visual Odometry (VO) which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): VO is an important component in robotics for navigation and localization. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel Curriculum Learning (CL) strategy for learning monocular VO which involves training a model by gradually increasing the difficulty of the training data. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a novel objective function for learning monocular VO which involves joint optimization of relative and composite transformations over small windows. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper presents a novel approach for learning monocular VO which outperforms state-of-the-art feature-based and learning-based VO on three real-world datasets.
